          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1682099757975-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1682099757975-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large pot with a small drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>remaining gochujang paste </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) to the pot and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>remaining tamari soy sauce</strong>, <strong>pho broth paste</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> and 700ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[900ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.2L]</span><strong> boiled water</strong> and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>spicy broth</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1682099760954-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1682099760954-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1682099760954-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1682099760954-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1682099760954-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Bring the <strong>spicy broth</strong> to the boil, then reduce the heat to medium-high</p><p>Add your <strong>carrot & cabbage slaw mix</strong> to the pot and cook for 1-2 min or until the veg is softened</p><p>Once the veg has softened, add the <strong>softened</strong> <strong>noodles</strong> to the pot and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>spicy rice noodle soup</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1682099765613-x200.jpg",
